    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="122" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward to Mr. Adams</persName>..</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1792.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 26, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 1843 from
                            this department in regard to be disposition to be made by you of the
                            first instalment of the Simonoseki iniemnity, which has been paid by the
                            Japanese government, I now transmit for your information, and with a
                            view to the carrying out of the instructions upon that subject
                            heretofore sent you, a copy of a despatch<note n="*" xml:id="d122fn1">For enclosure see correspondence with Japan.</note> of the 13th of
                            April from Mr. Portman, our chargé d’affaires ad <hi rend="italic">interim</hi> at Yedo, together with the original receipt, in
                            quadruplicate, signed by the officer in charge of the British commission
                            at Yokohama, for the sum of five hundred thousand dollars, $500,000,) or
                            one hundred and six thousand and two hundred and fifty pounds sterling
                            (£106,250.)</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
